<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-19T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51 Public Works Debt/141:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-19T13:00:00-05:00">October 19, 1938—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>117. For the Under Secretary. I carefully reviewed with the Secretary of
                            State this morning our policy as set forth in your telegram 74, October
                            6, noon, and in your personal letter to me of October 13. Doctor Remos
                            took careful notes and expressed the wish that I see the President and
                            outline our policy once more to him. The only interpretation I can reach
                            is that again there has been a misunderstanding of our attitude on the
                            part of the officials of this Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>